obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (11094)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. 2nd April, 1948, see Gazette of India, Part I.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=11094&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Damodar Valley`
  line `Corporation Act, 1948.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the States of Bihar and West Bengal.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (11095)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Interpretation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=11095&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context,--`
  line
  line `(1) "Corporation" means the Damodar Valley Corporation;`
  line
  line `(2) "Damodar Valley" includes the basin of the Damodar river and its tributaries;`
  line
  line `(3) "member" means a member of the Corporation and includes the Chairman;`
  line
  line `(4) "participating Governments" means the Central Government, the State Government of Bihar and`
  line `the State Government of West Bengal;`
  line
  line `(5) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under section 59;`
  line
  line `(6) "State Government" means the Government of Bihar or as the case may be of West Bengal, and`
  line `"State Government" means the Governments of Bihar and West Bengal;`
  line
  line `(7) "regulations" means the regulations made by the Corporation under section 60.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (11096)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Incorporation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=11096&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the Central Government may, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, appoint in this behalf, there shall be established a Corporation by the name of the`
  line `Damodar Valley Corporation.`
  line
  line `(2) The said Corporation shall be a body corporate having perpetual succession and a common seal,`
  line `and shall by the said name sue and be sued.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (11097)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Constitution of the Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=11097&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) The Corporation shall consist of--`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairman;`
  line
  line `(b) a member (technical) and a member (finance);`
  line
  line `(c) one representative from the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(d) two representatives one each from the State Government of Jharkhand and West Bengal;`
  line
  line `(e) three independent experts one each from the field of irrigation, water supply and generation or`
  line `transmission or distribution of electricity; and`
  line
  line `(f) a Member-Secretary.`
  line
  line `(1A) The Chairman and members under clauses (a), (b), (d) and (f) of sub-section (1) shall be`
  line `appointed by the Central Government in consultation with the State Governments concerned while the`
  line `members under clauses (c) and (e) shall be appointed by the Central Government, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(1B) The Chairman and members under clauses (a), (b) and (f) of sub-section (1) shall be`
  line `whole-time while the members under clauses (c), (d) and (e) shall be part-time.`
  line
  line `(1C) The Chairman shall be the Chief Executive Officer of the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(1D) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in sub-section (1C), the Member-Secretary shall`
  line `be in charge of general administration and business development of the Corporation.]`
  line
  line `(2) A person shall be disqualified for being appointed, or for continuing as, a member of the`
  line Corporation--
  line
  line `(a) if he is a member of ^2[Parliament] or any State Legislature; or`
  line
  line `(b) if he has, directly or indirectly, any interest in a subsisting contract made with, or in any work`
  line `being done for, the Corporation except as a shareholder (other than a director) in an incorporated`
  line `company provided that where he is a shareholder, he shall disclose to the Government the nature and`
  line `extent of shares held by him in such Company.`
  line
  line `(3) No act or proceeding of the Corporation shall be invalid by reason only of the existence of any`
  line `vacancy amongst its members or any defect in the appointment of a member thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 2012, s. 2, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 19-8-2013).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "the Central".`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (11098)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Conditions of service of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes `1. Sub-section (1) omitted by Act 59 of 1957, s. 2.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=11098&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `^1* * * * * *`
  line
  line `(2) The remuneration and other conditions of service of the members shall be such as may be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (11099)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Appointment of officers and servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1. Subs-sections (1) and (2) omitted by Act 1 of 2012, s. 3 (w.e.f. 19-8-2013).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=11099&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `^1* * * * * *`
  line
  line `(2) The remuneration and other conditions of service of the members shall be such as may be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (11100)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Conditions of service of officers and servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes `1. Clause (a) omitted by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 19-8-2013).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=11100&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `The pay and other conditions of service of the`
  line `officers and servants of the Corporation shall--`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
  line
  line `(b) as respects the other officers and servants, be such as may be determined by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (11101)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Functions and duties of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for section 8 (w.e.f. 19-8-2013).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=11101&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `^1[8. Functions and duties of members.--The functions and duties of members shall be such as may`
  line `be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (11102)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `General disqualification of all officers and servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=11102&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `No person who has directly or indirectly,`
  line `by himself or his partner or agent, any share or interest in any contract, by or on behalf of the`
  line `Corporation, or in any employment under, by or on behalf of the Corporation otherwise than as an officer`
  line `or servant thereof, shall become or remain an officer or servant of the Corporation.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (11103)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Appointment of Advisory Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=11103&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Subject to any rules made under section 59 the`
  line `Corporation may from time to time appoint one or more Advisory Committees for the purpose of securing`
  line `the efficient discharge of the functions of the Corporation, and in particular for the purpose of securing`
  line `that those functions are exercised with due regard to the circumstances and requirements of particular`
  line `local areas.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (11104)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Limits of Damodar Valley and area of operations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=11104&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, specify the limits of the Damodar Valley.`
  line
  line `(2) The Corporation shall carry out all or any of its functions and exercise all or any of its powers`
  line `within the Damodar Valley.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, after consultation with the State Governments by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, direct that the Corporation shall carry out such function and exercise such power in such`
  line `other area as may be specified therein and the area so specified shall be called the "area of operation" of`
  line `the Corporation.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (11105)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Functions of the Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=11105&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The functions of the Corporation shall be--`
  line
  line `(a) the promotion and operation of schemes for irrigation, water-supply and drainage,`
  line
  line `(b) the promotion and operation of schemes for the generation, transmission and distribution of`
  line `electrical energy, both hydro-electric and thermal,`
  line
  line `(c) the promotion and operation of schemes for flood control in the Damodar river and its`
  line `tributaries and the channels, if any, excavated by the Corporation in connection with the scheme and`
  line `for the improvement of flow conditions in the Hooghly river,`
  line
  line `(d) the promotion and control of navigation in the Damodar river and its tributaries and channels,`
  line `if any,`
  line
  line `(e) the promotion of afforestation and control of soil erosion in the Damodar Valley, and`
  line
  line `(f) the promotion of public health and the agricultural, industrial, economic and general wellbeing`
  line `in the Damodar Valley and its area of operation.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (11106)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Provision for irrigation and water-supply.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=11106&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The Corporation may, with the approval of the`
  line `State Government concerned which shall not be unreasonably withheld, construct canals and`
  line `distributaries and maintain and operate them:`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Government may, after giving notice and subject to the payment of fair`
  line `compensation, take over the maintenance and operation of any such canal or distributary.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (11107)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Rates for supply of water for irrigation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=11107&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Corporation may, after consultation with the`
  line `State Government concerned, determine and levy rates for the bulk supply of water to that Government`
  line `for irrigation, and fix the minimum quantity of water which shall be made available for such purpose.`
  line
  line `(2) The rates at which such water shall be supplied by the State Government to the cultivators and`
  line `other consumers shall be fixed by that Government after consultation with the Corporation.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (11108)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Rates for supply of water for industrial and domestic purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=11108&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `The Corporation may`
  line `determine and levy rates for bulk supply and retail distribution of water for industrial and domestic`
  line `purposes and specify the manner of recovery of such rates.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (11109)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Supply of water to those whose supply has been stopped or reduced.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=11109&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `If, with a view to`
  line `operating its schemes, the Corporation has stopped or reduced the supply of water to any person for`
  line `agricultural, industrial or domestic purposes which such person was, prior to such stoppage or reduction,`
  line `enjoying by virtue of any prescriptive right, the Corporation shall arrange such supply of water on the`
  line `same terms as before.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (11110)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Construction of dam, etc., prohibited except with the approval of the Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=11110&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Save as`
  line `otherwise prescribed, no person shall construct, operate or maintain in the Damodar Valley any dam or`
  line `other work or any installation for the extraction of water without the consent of the Corporation.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (11111)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Supply and generation of electrical energy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=11111&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Indian`
  line `Electricity Act, 1910 (9 of 1910), or any licence granted thereunder--`
  line
  line `(i) No person shall without the permission of the Corporation--`
  line
  line `(a) sell electrical energy to any consumer in the Damodar Valley where the energy is taken`
  line `by the consumer at a pressure of 30,000 volts or more;`
  line
  line `(b) transmit electrical energy in the Damodar Valley at a pressure of 30,000 volts or more;`
  line
  line `(c) generate any electrical energy at an installation having an aggregate capacity of more than`
  line `10,000 kilowatts in any part of the Damodar Valley lying to the north of a straight line drawn east`
  line `to west passing through a point at latitude twenty-two degrees, fourteen minutes and forty-seven`
  line `seconds and longitude eighty-seven degrees, fifty-one minutes and forty-two seconds except such`
  line `portion of the municipal area of Burdwan as may lie to the north of such straight line:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in sub-clause (c) shall apply to any person who was, at the commencement of`
  line `this Act, generating electrical energy at an installation having an aggregate capacity of more than 10,000`
  line `kilowatts, so long as the capacity of such installation is not increased:`
  line
  line `Provided further that nothing in sub-clause (c) shall apply to the power station installation of the`
  line `fertiliser factory at Sindri having an aggregate capacity of 80,000 kilowatts so long as the capacity of such`
  line `installation is not increased beyond 80,000 kilowatts.`
  line
  line `(ii) The Corporation may sell electrical energy to any consumer in the Damodar Valley but no`
  line `such sale shall, except with the permission of the State Government concerned, be made to any`
  line `consumer requiring supply at a pressure of less than 30,000 volts.`
  line
  line `(iii) The Corporation may, with the permission of the State Government concerned, extend its`
  line `transmission system to any area beyond the Damodar Valley and sell electrical energy in such area.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (11112)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Effect on existing licences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=11112&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1)Where any licence granted under the Indian Electricity Act,`
  line `1910 (9 of 1910), becomes inoperative wholly or partly by virtue of the provisions of section 18, the`
  line `licence shall be deemed to have been revoked or modified so as to be consistent with those provisions.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a licence is deemed to have been revoked under sub-section (1) the Corporation shall`
  line `purchase the undertaking of the licencee, and where a licence is modified under that sub-section, the`
  line `Corporation shall, at the option of the licensee, either purchase the undertaking or pay fair compensation`
  line `to the licensee.`
  line
  line `(3) The purchase price or the amount of compensation payable by the corporation under`
  line `sub-section (2) shall be such as may be agreed to between the Corporation and the licensee or, in the`
  line `event of disagreement, as may be determined by arbitration.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (11113)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Charges for supply of electrical energy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=11113&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `The Corporation shall fix the schedule of charges for`
  line `the supply of electrical energy, including the rates for bulk supply and retail distribution, and specify the`
  line `manner of recovery of such charges:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Corporation may in any contract for bulk supply of electrical energy impose such`
  line `terms and conditions including a retail rate schedule as it may deem necessary or desirable to encourage`
  line `the use of electrical energy.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (11114)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Other activities of the Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=11114&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Corporation may establish, maintain and operate`
  line `laboratories, experimental and research stations and farms for conducting experiments and research for--`
  line
  line `(a) utilising the water, electrical energy and other resources in the most economical manner for`
  line `the development of the Damodar Valley,`
  line
  line `(b) determining the effect of its operations on the flow conditions in the Hooghly river,`
  line
  line `(c) making improvements in navigation conditions in the port of Calcutta, and`
  line
  line `(d) carrying out any other function specified under section 12.`
  line
  line `(2) The Corporation may set up its own planning, designing, construction and operating agencies, or`
  line `make arrangements therefor with the participating Governments, local authorities, educational and`
  line `research institutions or any person carrying on the business of an architect, an engineer or a contractor.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (11115)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `General powers of the Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=11115&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Corporation shall have the power to do anything`
  line `which may be necessary or expedient for the purposes of carrying out its functions under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing provision, such power shall include the`
  line power--
  line
  line `(i) to acquire and hold such movable and immovable property as it may deem necessary and to`
  line `lease, sell or otherwise transfer any such property;`
  line
  line `(ii) to construct or cause to be constructed such dams, barrages, reservoirs, power houses, power`
  line `structures, electrical transmission lines and sub-stations, navigation works, irrigation, navigation and`
  line `drainage canals and such other works and structures as may be required;`
  line
  line `(iii) to prevent pollution of any water under its control and to take all measures to prevent`
  line `discharges into such water effluents which are harmful to water supply, irrigation, public health or`
  line `fish life;`
  line
  line `(iv) to stock its reservoirs or water courses with fish and to regulate or prohibit taking out fish`
  line `from the water under its control;`
  line
  line `(v) to undertake resettlement of the population displaced by the dams, acquisition of land for`
  line `reservoirs and protection of watersheds;`
  line
  line `(vi) to aid in the establishment of co-operative societies and other organisations for the better use`
  line `of facilities made available by the Corporation;`
  line
  line `(vii) to undertake measures for the prevention of malaria.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (11116)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Power to close roads and open spaces.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=11116&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Corporation may, after giving notice to the`
  line `persons concerned or to the public generally,--`
  line
  line `(a) turn, divert or discontinue the public use of, or permanently close, any road or any part`
  line `thereof, or`
  line
  line `(b) discontinue the public use of, or permanently close, any open space or any part thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) Whenever the Corporation discontinues the public use of, or permanently closes, any road or open`
  line `space the Corporation shall pay reasonable compensation to every person--`
  line
  line `(a) who was entitled, otherwise than as a licensee, to use such road or open space or part`
  line `thereof as a means of access, or`
  line
  line `(b) Whose immovable property was receiving air and light on account of such open space or`
  line part,
  line
  line `and who has suffered damage--`
  line
  line `(i) in any case falling under clause (a) from such discontinuance or closure, and`
  line
  line `(ii) in any case falling under clause (b) from the use to which the Corporation has put such`
  line `open space or part.`
  line
  line `(3) In determining the compensation payable to any person under sub-section (2), the Corporation`
  line `may take into consideration any benefit accruing to such person from the construction, provision or`
  line `improvement of any other road, or open space at or about the same time that the road or open space or`
  line `part thereof, on account of which the compensation is to be paid, is discontinued or closed.`
  line
  line `(4) When any road or open space or any part thereof is permanently closed under sub-section (1), the`
  line `Corporation may sell or leave such part of it as is not required for its purposes.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (11117)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Powers under certain other enactments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=11117&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Acts`
  line `specified in column one of Part I of the Schedule, the Corporation may carry out all or any of the`
  line `functions and exercise all or any of the powers of a State Government in the Damodar Valley under the`
  line `provisions of such Acts specified in column two thereof against each item of column one.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Acts specified in column one of Part II of the`
  line `Schedule, any officer authorised by the Corporation may carry out all or any of the functions and exercise`
  line `all or any of the powers of a Canal Officer, Collector, or Forest Officer, as the case may be, in the`
  line `Damodar Valley under the provisions of such Acts specified in column two thereof against each item of`
  line `column one.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (11118)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Co-operation with other authorities to minimise inconvenience caused by submersion.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=11118&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line The
  line `Corporation shall co-operate with the participating Governments, railway authorities and local authorities`
  line `and bodies, with a view to minimising the inconvenience likely to be caused by the submersion of roads`
  line `and communications and shall bear the cost of any realignment thereof or resettlement of any population`
  line `rendered necessary by such submersion.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (11119)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Submersion of coal mines to be avoided by the Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=11119&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `The Corporation shall make`
  line `every endeavour to avoid submersion of coal or mineral deposits and shall co-operate with the coal`
  line `mining industry and the bodies set up by the participating Governments to ensure the maintenance of`
  line `supplies of sand for stowing purposes in coal mines and in other ways to minimise the inconvenience to`
  line `the coal mining industry.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (11120)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Expenditure till the Corporation is established.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=11120&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `All expenditure incurred by the Central`
  line `Government for and in connection with the establishment of the Corporation up to the date of its`
  line `establishment shall be treated as the capital provided by the Central Government to the Corporation and`
  line `such capital shall be adjusted between the participating Governments in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `sections 30 to 36.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (11121)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Vesting of property in the Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=11121&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `All property acquired and works constructed for the`
  line `purposes of the Damodar Valley scheme before the establishment of the Corporation shall vest in the`
  line `Corporation and all income derived and expenses incurred in this behalf shall be brought into the books of`
  line `the Corporation.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (11122)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Fund of the Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=11122&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Corporation shall have its own fund and all receipts of the`
  line `Corporation shall be carried thereto and all payments by the Corporation shall be made therefrom.`
  line
  line `(2) Except as otherwise directed by the Central Government, all moneys belonging to that fund shall`
  line `be deposited in the Reserve Bank of India or the Agents of the Reserve Bank of India or invested in such`
  line `securities as may be approved by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (11123)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Liabilities of participating Governments to provide capital to the Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=11123&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line The
  line `participating Governments shall, as hereinafter specified, provide the entire capital required by the`
  line `Corporation for the completion of any project undertaken by it.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (11124)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Payment by participating Government on specified date.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=11124&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `Each participating Government`
  line `shall provide its share of the capital on the dates specified by the Corporation and if any Government fails`
  line `to provide such share on such dates the Corporation may raise loan to make up the deficit at the cost of`
  line `the Government concerned.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (11125)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Expenditure on objects other than irrigation, power and flood control.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=11125&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `The Corporation`
  line `shall have power to spend such sums as it thinks fit on objects authorised under this Act other than`
  line `irrigation, power and flood control and such sums shall be treated as common expenditure payable out of`
  line `the fund of the Corporation before allocation under section 32.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (11126)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Allocation of expenditure chargeable to project on main objects.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=11126&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `The total capital`
  line `expenditure chargeable to a project shall be allocated between the three main objects, namely, irrigation,`
  line `power and flood control as follows, namely:---`
  line
  line `(1) expenditure solely attributable to any of these objects, including a proportionate share of`
  line `overhead and general charges, shall be charged to that object, and`
  line
  line `(2) expenditure common to two or more of the said objects, including a proportionate share of`
  line `overhead and general charges, shall be allocated to each of such objects in proportion to the`
  line `expenditure which, according to the estimates of the Corporation, would have been incurred in`
  line `constructing a separate structure solely for that object, less any amount determined under clause (1) in`
  line `respect of that object.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (11127)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Capital allocated to irrigation`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=11127&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `The total amount of capital allocated to irrigation shall be`
  line `shared between the State Governments as follows, namely:--`
  line
  line `(1) the Government concerned shall be responsible for the capital cost of the works constructed`
  line `exclusively for irrigation in its State; and`
  line
  line `(2) the balance of capital cost under irrigation for both the States of Bihar and West Bengal shall be`
  line `shared by the State Governments in the proportion to their guaranteed annual off-takes of water for`
  line `agricultural purposes:`
  line
  line `Provided that the divisible capital cost under this clause shall be provisionally shared between them in`
  line `accordance with their previously declared intentions regarding their respective guaranteed off-takes and`
  line `any payments made accordingly shall be adjusted after the determination of the guaranteed off-takes.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (29040)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Capital allocated to power.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=29040&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `The total amount of capital allocated to power shall be shared`
  line `equally between the three participating Governments.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (29041)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Capital allocated to flood control.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=29041&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `The total amount of capital up to fourteen crores of rupees`
  line `allocated to flood control shall be shared equally between the Central Government and the Government of`
  line `West Bengal and any amount in excess thereof shall be the liability of the Government of West Bengal.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (29042)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Disposal of profits and deficits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=29042&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (2) of section 40,`
  line `the net profit, if any, attributable to each of the three main objects, namely, irrigation, power and flood`
  line `control, shall be credited to the participating Governments in proportion to their respective shares in the`
  line `total capital cost attributed to that object.`
  line
  line `(2) The net deficit, if any, in respect of any of the objects shall be made good by the Governments`
  line `concerned in the proportion specified in sub-section (1):`
  line
  line `Provided that the net deficit in respect of flood control shall be made good entirely by the`
  line `Government of West Bengal and the Central Government shall have no share in such deficit.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (29043)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Payment of interest`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=29043&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `The Corporation shall pay interest on the amount of capital provided by`
  line `each participating Government at such rate as may, from time to time, be fixed by the Central`
  line `Government and such interest shall be deemed to be part of the expenditure of the Corporation.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (29044)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Interest charge and other expenses to be added to and receipts taken for reduction of capital cost.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=29044&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `For a period, not exceeding fifteen years, from the establishment of the Corporation, if the`
  line `Corporation runs in deficit, the interest 28 charges and all other expenditure shall be added to the capital`
  line `cost and all receipts shall be taken in reduction of such capital cost.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (29045)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Provision for depreciation and reserve and other funds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=29045&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Corporation shall make`
  line `provision for depreciation and for reserve and other funds at such rates and on such terms as may be`
  line `specified by the Auditor-General of India in consultation with the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The net profit for the purposes of section 37 shall be determined after such provision has been`
  line made.
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (29046)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Corporation's share in betterment levy by State Governments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=29046&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `In the event of any`
  line `betterment levy being imposed by a State Government, the proportionate proceeds thereof in so far as`
  line `they are attributable to the operations of the corporation shall be credited to the Corporation.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (29047)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `. Borrowing of money`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=29047&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `The Corporation may, with the approval of the Central Government,`
  line `borrow money in the open market or otherwise for the purposes of carrying out its functions under this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (29048)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Liability to pay Central taxes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=29048&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Corporation shall be liable to pay any taxes on income`
  line `levied by the Central Government in the same manner and to the same extent as a company.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Governments shall not be entitled to any refund of any such taxes paid by the`
  line Corporation.
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (29049)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title Budget.
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=29049&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Corporation, in consultation with the ^1[member (finance)], shall in October`
  line `each year prepare in such form as may be prescribed a budget for the next financial year showing the`
  line `estimated receipts and expenditure and the amounts which would be required from each of the three`
  line `participating Governments during that financial year.`
  line
  line `(2) Printed copies of the budget shall be made available to each of the three participating`
  line `Governments by the 15th day of November each year.`
  line
  line `(3) The budget shall be laid before ^2[Parliament] and the State Legislatures concerned as soon as may`
  line `be after it is prepared.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 2012, s. 6, for "financial adviser" (w.e.f. 19-8-2013).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A. O. 1950, for "the Central".`
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (29050)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Annual report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A. O. 1950, for "the Central".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=29050&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Corporation shall prepare, in such form as may be prescribed, an annual`
  line `report within six months after the end of each financial year giving a true and faithful account of its`
  line `activities during the previous financial year, with particular reference to--`
  line
  line `(i) irrigation;`
  line
  line `(ii) water supply;`
  line
  line `(iii) electrical energy;`
  line
  line `(iv) flood control;`
  line
  line `(v) navigation;`
  line
  line `(vi) afforestation;`
  line
  line `(vii) soil erosion;`
  line
  line `(viii) use of lands;`
  line
  line `(ix) resettlement of displaced population;`
  line
  line `(x) sanitation and public health measures; and`
  line
  line `(xi) economic and social welfare of the people.`
  line
  line `(2) The annual report shall also give a true and faithful account of the income and expenditure during`
  line `the previous financial year, the net amounts attributable to each of the three main objects and the`
  line `distribution of the capital cost between the three participating Governments and show the progressive`
  line `totals from the inception of the Corporation and the up-to-date financial results.`
  line
  line `(3) The payments provisionally made by each of the three participating Governments on the basis of`
  line `the budget estimates shall be adjusted as soon as possible in accordance with the allocation made in the`
  line `annual report.`
  line
  line `(4) Printed copies of the annual report shall be made available to each of the three participating`
  line `Governments by the 15th day of October each year.`
  line
  line `(5) The annual report shall be laid before ^1[Parliament] and the State Legislatures concerned as soon`
  line `as may be after it is prepared.`
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (29051)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Other annual financial statements.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=29051&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Corporation shall also prepare such other annual`
  line `financial statements in such form and by such dates as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Printed copies of each such annual financial statement shall be made available to each of the three`
  line `participating Governments by such date as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (29052)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=29052&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `The accounts of the Corporation shall be maintained and audited in such`
  line `manner as may, in consultation with the Auditor-General of India, be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (29053)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Directions by the Central Government`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=29053&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) In discharge of its functions the Corporation shall`
  line `be guided by such instructions on questions of policy as may be given to it by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) If any dispute arises between the Central Government and the Corporation as to whether a`
  line `question is or is not a question of policy, the decision of the Central Government shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (29054)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Disputes between the Corporation and Governments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=29054&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise expressly`
  line `provided in this Act, any dispute between the Corporation and any participating Government regarding`
  line `any matter covered by this Act or touching or arising out of it shall be referred to an arbitrator who shall`
  line `be appointed by the Chief Justice of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The decision of the arbitrator shall be final and binding on the parties.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (29055)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `. Compulsory acquisition of land for the Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=29055&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `Any land required by the Corporation`
  line `for carrying out its functions under this Act shall be deemed to be needed to be needed for a public`
  line `purpose and such land shall be acquired for the Corporation as if the provisions of Part VII of the Land`
  line `Acquisition Act, 1894 (1 of 1894), were applicable to it and the Corporation were a company within the`
  line `meaning of clause (e) of section 3 of the said Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (29056)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `. Control of Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=29056&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may remove from the`
  line `Corporation any member who in its opinion--`
  line
  line `(a) refuses to act,`
  line
  line `(b) has become incapable of acting,`
  line
  line `(c) has so abused his position as a member as to render his continuance on the Corporation`
  line `detrimental to the interest of the public, or`
  line
  line `(d) is otherwise unsuitable to continue as member.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may suspend any member pending an enquiry against him.`
  line
  line `(3) No order of removal under this section shall be made unless the member concerned has been`
  line `given an opportunity to submit his explanation to the Central Government, and when such order is passed`
  line `the seat of the member removed shall be declared vacant and another member may be appointed under`
  line `section 4 to fill up the vacancy.`
  line
  line `(4) A member who has been removed shall not be eligible for reappointment as member or in any`
  line `other capacity to the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government may declare void any transaction in connection with which a member`
  line `has been removed under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(6) If the Corporation fails to carry out its functions, or follow the directions issued by the Central`
  line `Government under this Act, the Central Government shall have the power to remove the Chairman and`
  line `the members of the Corporation and appoint a Chairman and members in their places.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (29057)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Application of certain provisions of the Indian Forest Act, 1927, to the forests of the Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=29057&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `All acts prohibited in respect of a reserved forest under section 26 of the Indian Forest`
  line `Act, 1927 (16 of 1927) shall be deemed to be prohibited in respect of any forest owned by or under the`
  line `supervision or control of the Corporation and all offences in respect of such forest shall be punishable`
  line `under the said Act as if they were committed in respect of a reserved forest.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (29058)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title Penalty.
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=29058&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `Whoever contravenes the provisions of sections 17 and 18 of this Act or any rule made`
  line `thereunder shall be punished with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months or with fine`
  line `or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (29059)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Procedure for prosecution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=29059&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `No Court shall take cognisance of an offence under this Act except`
  line `on the complaint of an officer of the Corporation authorised by it in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (29060)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Power of entry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=29060&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `Any officer or servant of the Corporation generally or specially authorised by`
  line `the Corporation may at all reasonable times enter upon any land or premises and there do such things as`
  line `may be reasonably necessary for the purpose of lawfully carrying out any of its works or of making any`
  line `survey, examination or investigation preliminary or incidental to the exercise of powers or the`
  line `performance of functions by the Corporation under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (29061)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Members, officers and servants of the Corporation to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=29061&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `All members,`
  line `officers and servants of the Corporation, whether appointed by the Central Government or the`
  line `Corporation, shall be deemed, when acting or purporting to act in pursuance of any of the provisions of`
  line `this Act to be public servants within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (29062)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Protection of action of action taken under the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=29062&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit, prosecution, or legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against any person in the employment of the Corporation for anything which is in good faith done or`
  line `purported to be done under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Save as otherwise provided in the Act no suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against the`
  line `Corporation for any damage caused or likely to be caused by anything in good faith done or purported to`
  line `be done under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (29063)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `. Effect of other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=29063&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act or any rule made thereunder shall have effect`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in any enactment other than this Act or any instrument having effect`
  line `by virtue of any enactment other than this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (29064)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `. Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=29064&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification in the official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(1) the salaries and allowances and conditions of service of members,`
  line ^1***;
  line
  line `(2) the functions and duties of the ^2[members];`
  line
  line `(3) the dams or other works or the installations which may be constructed without the approval of the`
  line Corporation;
  line
  line `(4) the forms of the budget, the annual report and the annual financial statements and the dates by`
  line `which copies of the annual financial statements shall be made available to the participating Governments;`
  line
  line `(5) the manner in which the accounts of the Corporation shall be maintained and audited;`
  line
  line `(6) the appointment of an Advisory Committee; and`
  line
  line `(7) the punishment for breach of any rule made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "the secretary and the financial adviser" omitted by Act 1 of 2012, s. 7 (w.e.f. 19-8-2013).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for "financial adviser" (w.e.f. 19-8-2013)`
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (29065)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824&sectionId=29065&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00004_194814_1517807325824
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Corporation may, with the previous sanction of the`
  line `Central Government, by notification in the Gazette of India, make regulations for carrying out its`
  line `functions under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, in such regulation the`
  line `Corporation may make provision for--`
  line
  line `(a) making of appointments and promotions of its officers and servants;`
  line
  line `(b) specifying other conditions of service of its officers and servants;`
  line
  line `(c) specifying the manner in which water rates and charges for electrical energy shall be`
  line recovered;
  line
  line `(d) preventing the pollution of water under its control;`
  line
  line `(e) regulating the taking out of fish from the water under its control;`
  line
  line `(f) regulating its proceedings and business;`
  line
  line `(g) prescribing punishment for breach of any regulation.`
  line
  line `(3) All regulations made under sub-sections (1) and (2) shall, as soon as possible, be published also in`
  line `the Official Gazettes of the State Governments.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations:
  hi obj_root_law_translations_hi
obj_root_law_translations_hi:
